    "Accordingly, there is a need for more comprehensive and inclusive RAI research to advance RAI practices in real-world settings.measure and find evidence of the impact of RAI practices in real-world settings.Fifth, an intriguing finding of our review is the absence of articles addressing the landscape of AI commercialisation in terms of investment, policies, and ownership related to AI data or companies, such as practices for selling and buying data in secondary markets or ensuring data sovereignty.",
    "These are increasingly critical issues, particularly as AI companies are frequently acquired by new investors or holding companies.",
    "This identified gap highlights an important area for future research, particularly in relation to the growing influence of investors and the commodification of AI data under the umbrella of business ethics or corporate law.",
    "ConclusionsBecause of the transformative impact of AI-enabled systems in real-world settings, RAI has become an important topic in ensuring that AI-enabled systems are developed, deployed, and used in a responsible manner, upholding the fundamental rights and legitimate interests of their stakeholders.",
